  "text": "Complete forced degradation study was performed on Ezetimibe taking into consideration the above mentioned aspects. Ezetimibe was subjected to thermolytic, photolytic, hydrolytic (acidic and alkaline) and oxidative stress conditions. The stressed and unstressed samples of Ezetimibe were injected into a developed and validated High Performance Liquid Chromatography (HPLC) method. In this method, a Hypersil C 18 column (150 mm x 4.6 mm i.d., 5 m particle size) kept at a temperature of 40°C was used. Chromatographic separation was achieved under isocratic elution using a mobile phase consisting of a mixture of KH 2 PO 4 buffer (pH 2.5; 0.05 M) -Methanol (45:55, v/v). UV detector was set at 242 nm. Flow rate was adjusted to 1.0 mL/min. Injection volume of standard and test solutions was kept as 10 L. Water-methanol mixture (50:50, v/v) was used as the diluent [CITATION_1] .",
